What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataframe consist of 84853 entries and 25 columns.Most data types are str and numerical type. All these types of data gives us loan and borrower information.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested in understanding the interest rate and APR of a loan, and the loan status. I have found that the range for interest rate is 0.1-0.36 and for APR is between 0.1-0.4, with APR being slightly higher than the interest rate. From loanstatus we can seen how many loans are completed, chargedoff or default. Additionally, I would like to know the main factors affecting the interest rate, the average interest rate on big and small loans, the size of loans taken out from Prosper, who typically takes out big and small loans, any differences in loans based on employment status, and which category of listing takes the most loans and for what purpose.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

From this dataset there are many features that can help us to answer our questions. To understand how interest rate is effected it would be the borrower information such as --> (CreditScore, IncomeRange, DebtToIncomeRatio, ProsperRating, StatedMonthlyIncome) that will help with our investigation. Along with these EmploymentStatus will also help us to understand loanStatus as well.

In [32]:
# Create a list of loan status categories
loanstatus_dict = ['Current','Completed','Defaulted','Chargedoff','Past Due','FinalPaymentInProgress']

# Create a categorical data type with the loan status categories
loanstatus_order = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories = loanstatus_dict, ordered = True)

# Aggregate Past Due loans and convert LoanStatus to a categorical variable
df_new['LoanStatus'] = df_new['LoanStatus'].apply(lambda x: 'Past Due' if 'Past Due' in x else x)
df_new['LoanStatus'] = df_new['LoanStatus'].astype(loanstatus_order)
